I. Enabling backup jobs
    1. Login to OpenShift Container Platform cluster as an nomocpadmin user
    2. Command execution -->  " oc get br -A|grep noobaa-db-backup-restore "
    3. Expected Outcome -->      "openshift-storage   noobaa-db-backup-restore                  24d"
    4. Logout



II. Checking the backup storage mode
    1. Login to OpenShift Container Platform cluster as an nomocpadmin user
    2. Command execution -->  "br_operations policy list | grep cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates"
    3. Expected Outcome -->      "nom-apps                            cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates"
    4. Command execution -->  "oc describe br cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates -n nom-apps | grep -A 1 Backend"
    5. Expected Outcome -->      "  Backend:
                                    Mode:     local"
    6.Logout



III. Taking Secret Key Management secret backup
    1. Login to OpenShift Container Platform cluster as an nomocpadmin user
    2. Command execution -->  "python /opt/shared-product/backup_restore/bin/backup_cskm_secret.py"
    3. Expected Outcome -->      "2022-10-18 14:44:28,747 - UTC - atntcluster1node6 - admin - backup_cskm_secret - INFO - Successfully verified that the CSKM secret backup file is copied to local backup directory.
                               2022-10-18 14:44:28,747 - UTC - atntcluster1node6 - admin - backup_cskm_secret - INFO - Executing : rm -f /tmp/cskm-secret.yaml
                               2022-10-18 14:44:28,752 - UTC - atntcluster1node6 - admin - backup_cskm_secret - INFO -
                               2022-10-18 14:44:28,752 - UTC - atntcluster1node6 - admin - backup_cskm_secret - INFO - Successfully removed the temporary file /tmp/cskm-secret.yaml"
    4. Logout
    
IV. Taking on-demand backups
    1. Login to OpenShift Container Platform cluster as an nomocpadmin user
    2. Command execution -->  "br_operations policy list | grep cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates"
    3. Expected Outcome -->      "nom-apps                            cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates"
    4. Command execution -->  "br_operations backup ondemand -n nom-apps -p cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates|grep message"
    5. Expected Outcome -->      "message": "backup task = 1558b4c1-26b5-4de3-8b35-652529967de6 is on!"
    6. Split The output and obtain <task id>
    7. Command execution -->  "br_operations status task --id 1558b4c1-26b5-4de3-8b35-652529967de6|grep status"
    8. Expected Outcome -->      "  "status": "Success""
    9. Logout
    
V. Disabling backup jobs
    1. Login to OpenShift Container Platform cluster as an nomocpadmin user
    2. Command execution -->  "br_operations cron enable -n nom-apps -p cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates"
    3. Expected Outcome -->      "cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates : Success"
    4. Command execution -->  "br_operations policy list | grep cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates"
    5. Expected Outcome -->      "nom-apps                            cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates"
    6. Command execution -->  "br_operations cron disable -n nom-apps -p cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates"
    7. Expected Outcome -->      "cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates : Success"
    8. Command execution -->  "oc get cronjobs -n cal-shared-product"
    9. Expected Outcome -->      " NAME               SCHEDULE      SUSPEND   ACTIVE   LAST SCHEDULE   AGE
                                openshift-backup   26 08 * * *   False     0        6h29m           24d"
    10. Logout



VI. Deleting backup data
    1. Login to OpenShift Container Platform cluster as an nomocpadmin user
    2. Command execution -->  "br_operations policy list | grep cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates"
    3. Expected Outcome -->      "nom-apps                            cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates"
    4. Command execution -->  "br_operations backup list -n nom-apps -p cal-aws-backup-restore-user-preferences"
    5. Expected Outcome -->      "message": "backup task = 1558b4c1-26b5-4de3-8b35-652529967de6 is on!"
    6. From the output, obtain <task id>
    7. Command execution -->  "br_operations backup delete -n nom-apps -p cal-aws-backup-restore-user-preferences -i ${backup_id} |grep status"
    8. Expected Outcome -->      ""status": "Success""
    9. Logout



VII. Verifying backup is available
    1. Login to OpenShift Container Platform cluster as an nomocpadmin user
    2. Command execution -->  "br_operations policy list | grep cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates"
    3. Expected Outcome -->      "nom-apps                            cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates"
    4. Command execution -->  "oc exec -it $(oc get pods -n cal-shared-product | grep cbur-master-cbur-mycelery | cut -d " " -f1 | head -1) -c cbur -n cal-shared-product -- ls -lhtr /CBUR_REPO/data/nom-apps/STATEFULSET_cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates |awk '{print $9}'|head -2"
    5. Expected Outcome -->      "20221017115122"
    6. Command execution -->  "oc exec -it $(oc get pods -n cal-shared-product | grep cbur-master-cbur-mycelery | cut -d " " -f1 | head -1) -c cbur -n cal-shared-product -- ls -lhtr /CBUR_REPO/data/nom-apps/STATEFULSET_cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates/20221017115122"
    8. Expected Outcome -->      "total 4.0K
                               -rw-rw-r--. 1 1000660000 1000660000 1.3K Oct 17 11:51 20221017115122_e03_LOCAL_nom-apps_cal-aws-backup-restore-cmtemplates-0_volume.tar.gz"
    9. Logout
